__section__
default
__description__
Used to produce an easily parse-able, comprehensive list of tags, e.g., as
needed by the tag widget.

You supply user_tags, top_tags, and system_tags.

In the output, the lists will be separated by newlines.  The tags within each
list will be separated by whatever you used in the caller (hopefully spaces).

If you only supply one list, what you get back will be only that list,
unadorned. If you supply more than one, or else if you set require_markers to
true, then each list in the output will be prefixed with a header of the form
'<class>', where class is 'user', 'top', or 'system'.

The tag-widget's ajax code parses this form directly, but this template may be
useful elsewhere, possibly to simplify logic in single-list no_markup cases.
__title__
Useless title to template
__page__
misc
__lang__
en_US
__name__
combined_tags
__seclev__
10000
__template__
[% require_markers = require_markers || (((user_tags ? 1 : 0) + (top_tags ? 1 : 0) + (system_tags ? 1 : 0)) > 1) -%]
[% IF user_tags %][% IF require_markers %]<user>[% END %][% user_tags %]
[% END %][% IF top_tags %][% IF require_markers %]<top>[% END %][% top_tags %]
[% END %][% IF system_tags %][% IF require_markers %]<system>[% END %][% system_tags %][% END %]
